  "text": "where \u03b1 is a constant penalty factor for each estimated parameter. The value of \u03b1 is determined as a compromise between the probabilities and the costs of overfit and underfit [CITATION_1] . The cost of overfit is determined for a VAR(p) process by the accuracy of models of orders p + 1 and higher with too many estimated parameters that have zero as their true values. The cost of underfit is given by the deterministic error of the VAR(p \u2212 1) model of one order too low that belongs to a critical true parameter matrix A p . The critical value of A p would give [CITATION_2] ",
